gmd:metadataStandardName.gco:CharacterString: ISO 19139 Geographic Information - Metadata - Implementation Specification

gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString: Ayres Associates was contracted through the NCWRPC for the creation of 18' RGB DOQQs from the native resolution digital orthophotography from the 2010 Wisconsin Regional Orthoimagery Consortium (WROC) imagery program. Flights occurred in the Spring of 2010 for the entire State of Wisconsin, resulting in a 'leaf-off' aerial photo product. Re-flights were necessary for the eastern 4 mi of Columbia Co., parts of NW Oconto Co, and the south half of Lincoln Co. during the spring of 2011. Please refer to http://www.ncwrpc.org/WROC/Delivery_Specs.pdf for WROC program information

gmd:purpose.gco:CharacterString: The goal of this initiative is to develop color DOQQs for the entire State of Wisconsin.

gmd:supplementalInformation.gco:CharacterString: Both a county mosaic (JPEG2000, 10:1 compression) as well as individual GeoTIFF DOQQs are available for this dataset. Use the tabs within the WisconsinView data portal to select the desired format. For more information: http://www.ncwrpc.org/WROC/Delivery_Specs.pdf 2010 WROC imagery was flown in the spring of 2010, resulting in a "leaf-off" aerial photo product.

gmd:measureDescription.gco:CharacterString: The digital orthophotography meets or exceeds National Map Accuracy Standards for 1"=1000' scale mapping.
This standard requires that 90% of all test points are within 1/30th of an inch at mapping scale.

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: Ayres Associates created 18-inch resolution RGB DOQQs meeting 1:12,000-scale National Map Accuracy standards for horizontal accuracy. The DOQQs are a post product of native resolution WROC state-wide orthophotography. Please refer to the following link for quality standards: http://www.ncwrpc.org/WROC/Delivery_Specs.pdf

Any quad which intersected this particular county was copied into the appropriate county folder. All tiffs within the folder were then mosaicked and compressed to jpeg2000 (jp2) using a target compression ratio of 10:1. Due to the fact that the original DOQQ's (tiff) had background values of 255,255,255, the resulting mosaicked, compressed images have the same background value of 255,255,255. Unfortunately, the default and most used value for background values is 0,0,0. This will force the user of these compressed mosaics to manually set the background in ArcMap to 255,255,255.
Native resolution counties were mosaicked together to create 18" DOQQs. The data is complete for the entire State of Wisconsin.

gmd:maintenanceNote.gco:CharacterString: Metadata was created as or translated to ISO 19139 for inclusion in the Big Ten Academic Alliance Geoportal.
